name: BBQ Shrimp and Peach Skewers
author: Jason Swanger
summary: Grilled shrimp and fresh peach skewers glazed with BBQ sauce--a delicious way to prepare shrimp in the summer! The ingredients listed are for 1 skewer, but can easily be multiplied.
ingredients: 4  black tiger shrimp, peeled and deveined, tails off
½  fresh peach, pitted and cut into thirds
1 tablespoon barbecue sauce (such as Sweet Baby Ray's®), or more to taste
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate
Alternately thread shrimp and peach onto a skewer
Place on the hot grill and cook until shrimp are bright pink on the outside and the meat is opaque, about 5 minutes, turning occasionally and basting with barbecue sauce
